            <scopecontent id="aspace_4623acbfe496e5ca196ccef09512b5cc">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>The John Davenport Papers consist of photostatic copies of John Davenport's letters, which were collected by Isabel M. Calder and published in the <emph render="italic">Letters of John Davenport, Puritan Divine</emph> (New Haven: Yale University Press, 1937). The originals are located at repositories in the United States and Great Britain. The copies are of use primarily to those who wish to examine them in the handwritten style instead of the printed version.</p>
            </scopecontent>
